## Architecture Rules (Auto Global mode)
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Interactive components cannot access DbContext directly — use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, and with direct DB access on the server
- Both Program.cs files must register matching services
- No `@rendermode` needed on pages (global mode)

